sentences: Sander Ketelaars (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈsɑndər ˈkeːtəlaːrs]; born 28 February 1979), better known by his stage name Sander van Doorn (Dutch: [ˈsɑndər vɑn ˈdoːr(ə)n]) or the initials SvD, is a Dutch electro house DJ and record producer from Eindhoven.
Sander van Doorn began his recording career in 2004, releasing numerous tech-trance hits on Oxygen Recordings.
He became a regular DJ at Ibiza's Judgement Sunday and the Gallery in London, and was featured on BBC Radio One's Essential Mix in 2006.
He became a regular DJ at Ibiza's Judgement Sunday and the Gallery in London, and was featured on BBC Radio One's Essential Mix in 2006.

He gained recognition as a popular remixer, shifting from remixing for trance producers to pop/rock artists such as the Arctic Monkeys, whose hit "When the Sun Goes Down" was remixed by van Doorn in 2007.

He gained recognition as a popular remixer, shifting from remixing for trance producers to pop/rock artists such as the Arctic Monkeys, whose hit "When the Sun Goes Down" was remixed by van Doorn in 2007.
Sander van Doorn's musical style has ranged from tech-house and progressive house during the mid-2000s to more vocal-driven electro-house and EDM throughout the 2010s.
Despite being more known for DJing, since 2006, he's been a regular presence on DJMag's Top 100 DJ surveys.
Among his most notable remixes are Armin van Buuren's "Control Freak", Tiësto's "Dance4Life", Yello's "Oh Yeah", Sia's "The Girl You Lost to Cocaine", and Lady Gaga's "Marry the Night".

=== 2011: Second studio album =
On 19 September 2011, he released his second studio album titled "Eleve11" via Spinnin' Records.
In 2011, he performed at Energy, Mysteryland, EDC and started a residency at worldwide Sensation festivals.
Besides that, his Dusk till Doorn compilation got its 2011 version, all of which earned him a Dutch Silver Harp award.
Besides that, his Dusk till Doorn compilation got its 2011 version, all of which earned him a Dutch Silver Harp award.
In 2012, his singles regularly topped the charts of online dance music retailer, Beatport.
In March 2012, Sander performed at Ultra in Miami, where he introduced his new single "Nothing Inside" featuring Mayaeni.
In August 2012, it was announced that van Doorn and various notable electronic music producers would be featured on the Halo 4 remix album.
In 2013, he started a monthly program called "Identity" on internet dance music radio station Digitally Imported.
It became a weekly show that currently broadcasts to more than 70 radio stations globally.
The program ended its broadcast after its 623rd show on 5 November 2021.
In 2014, he collaborated with Martin Garrix and DVBBS for the single "Gold Skies".
He also released "Right Here Right Now".
In 2015, several more singles were released, including "Phoenix" (with R3hab) and "Rage" and collaborations with Firebeatz and Julian Jordan.
The Snake 2016 ===
Sander van Doorn started 2016 by releasing "Cuba Libre" followed by a collaboration with Gregor Salto for "Tribal".
"Raise Your Hands Up" with Chocolate Puma was released on Musical Freedom Records before "The Snake 2016" with Fred Pellichero.
He ended 2016 with "WTF", collaborating with Oliver Heldens, which was released on Heldeep Records on 28 November.
